This paper deals with optimizing queries for capturing database provenance, which is a topic closely related to database management systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses algebraic equivalences and heuristic optimization techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper presents a cost-based optimization framework, which is a common approach in distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE).
